# Auto Insurance Claim Severity Modeling

## Objective

To analyze insurance claim data and build predictive models to estimate claim severity and identify key drivers of risk.

---

## Data

Dataset includes policyholder demographics, vehicle characteristics, and claim amounts.

---

## Methodology

* Data cleaning and preprocessing
* Exploratory data analysis (EDA)
* Linear regression (baseline model)
* Random Forest (improved model)
* Feature importance and model interpretation

---

## Results

* Linear Regression: R² ≈ 0.56
* Random Forest: R² ≈ 0.81
* Key drivers: location, premium, vehicle class

Removing premium revealed underlying risk factors such as vehicle class and coverage.

---

## Key Insights

* Geographic location is the strongest predictor of claim severity
* Premium acts as a proxy variable capturing underlying risk
* Machine learning models significantly improve predictive performance

---

## Tools Used

* Python (pandas, scikit-learn, matplotlib)
